==Chinese==
{{wikipediapar|Guqin}}
===Etymology===
From [[еҸӨ]] вҖҳancientвҖҷ + [[зҗҙ]] вҖҳstringed instrumentвҖҷ

===Pronunciation===
*[[Pinyin]]: {{Audio|zh-gu3qin2.ogg|gЗ”qГӯn}}
*[[Wade-Giles]]: ku<sup>3</sup>-ch'in<sup>2</sup>
*{{IPA|[kutЙ•К°in]}}
*Plain: "goo-chin" 

===Noun===
#{{musici}} [[guqin]]; Chinese seven-stringed zither
#:*[[еҪҲ]]еҸӨзҗҙ (play the ''guqin'')
#(''place'') '''Guqin Tai''' гҖҠеҸӨзҗҙ[[иҮә]]гҖӢ (Guqin Terrace or Heptachord Terrace, etc.); the name of a place in [[Wuhan]], [[China]]

====Usage notes====
*In the past, the еҸӨзҗҙ was referred to only as зҗҙ, but it has the prefix еҸӨ- to distinguish it from other instruments which also use the word зҗҙ. It can be referred to as зҗҙ after еҸӨзҗҙ is used in the first instance.
*It is sometimes confused with the [[guzheng]] ([[еҸӨзӯқ]]) which is a different stringed instrument.

